name: New Talent Tuesday!
location: Spokane Comedy Club, Spokane WA
details: Every Tuesday, Featuring: Amateur and Professional comedians trying out new material. Free admission. Shows starting at 9:30pm or later are 21+, earlier shows are 18+ with valid ID. Visit Spokane Comedy Club for more info. View on Google Maps.

name: T'S ON A TUESDAY
location: T's Lounge, Spokane WA
details: Signup in person at 7:45pm. starts at 8pm usually 9ish on New Talent Nights. What's a comedy scene without a dive bar mic? T's On A Tuesday has been going strong for years and is the perfect place to test out your newest material. There is usually a large caravan of comics who come to T's after New Talent is done, and offers the type of stage where you can really let your hair down. Anything can (and likely will) happen at this mic, and it's never not a good time, but only if you enjoy telling jokes. tsspokane.com View on Google Maps

name: QUEER COMEDY NIGHT
location: nYne Bar & Bistro, Spokane WA
details: Signup in person at 7:30pm. starts at 8pm. nYne is one of our local gay bars, so any and all comics who identify as LGBTQIA+ are strongly encouraged to go. This open mic is one of 3 that are on Tuesday nights, so if you're looking to string performances together, don't miss it! Queer allies are also welcome! nynebar.com View on Google Maps

name: Open Mic Night!
location: Spokane Comedy Club, Spokane WA
details: Every Wednesday, A night with professional and first-time comedians. Free admission. Happy hour all night. Sign-up for comedians available at openmicer.com. View on Google Maps.

name: Open Mic Night..
location: Tervan Tavern 411 Cedar St, Sandpoint ID
details: Open Mic Night. Bring your talent in front of a live audience with a chill vibe. Be it song, instrument, comedy, improv, or magic, come show it off. Hosted by the Tervan Tavern, 411 Cedar St. starting at 6:00(ish) p.m. on Wednesdays. Visit Tervan Tavern for more info. View on Google Maps.

name: Open Mic Stand Up Comedy!
location: The Draft Zone, Post Falls ID
details: Weekly open mic stand-up comedy event. Every Thursday through 1/24. Free admission. Visit Draft Zone for more info. View on Google Maps.

name: Quincy Belt Tournament of Champions!
location: The Draft Zone, Post Falls ID
details: Post Falls, ID. Entry: Online/In Person. Free entry, no content restrictions. Qualify by winning the "Quincy Belt" at the open mic (Thursdays) or via video submission by 12/14. Semifinals: 2/3/24, 3/2/24, 4/6/24, 5/4/24. Finals: 6/1/24. Prizes: 1st - $1000, 2nd - $500, 3rd/4th - $250 each. Email: jaybergcomedy@gmail.com for details and entries. visit Draft Zone for more info. View on Google Maps.

name: LITTLE NEVADA COMEDY OPEN MIC
location: Little Nevada Restaurant and Lounge, Spokane WA
details: Signup in person at 6:00pm starts 6:30pm-ishThe Little Nevada Comedy Open Mic is Spokane's newest open mic! Located in the northern-ish part of Spokane, this spot (and every other one, for that matter) is only as good as you make it, so get to writing! little nevada Facebook View on Google Maps.

name: 3RD THURSDAY COMEDY OPEN MIC
location: Fox Hole Bar and Grill, Medical Lake WA
details: Signup in person or DM starts at 7:00pm sharp Happens on the 3RD THURSDAY OF THE MONTH. It is an open mic with a 20-min feature act at the end. Comics get the light when they have 1 min remaining. If you're looking to perform at the Fox Hole and DZ, let Chris know so he can put you towards the front of the lineup. Every comic that performs gets an even cut of tips @ the end of the show, so it pays (at least a little bit) to be (at least a little bit) funny. foxholemedicallake Facebook View on Google Maps.

name: Open Mic Night at The Grain Shed
location: The Grain Shed Taproom, Spokane WA

name: FRIDAY FUNNIES
location: The Garland Drinkery, Spokane WA
details: The Garland Drinkery is one of the newer mics in the area, and offers a fun space to perform in Spokane's Historic Garland District. Be sure to check our calendar so you know which Fridays those are! drinkerynation Facebook View on Google Maps.

name: Stand Up Comedy Open Mic

name: Open Mic Night at Emerge
location: Emerge downtown, Coeur D'Alene ID
details: Every third Thursday of the month - Singers, Songwriters, Poets, Spoken Word & Monologues welcome. All ages welcome. We just ask that you be respectful of others in the space and are ready to experience a wide variety of performances. You may be introduced to a new form of expression you never even knew you would like! Open Mic is sponsored by Emerge CDA and North Idaho Pride Alliance. FREE. RSVP is recommended, but not required. Visit website. View on Google Maps.
